erred Skills<br /></strong><ul><li>Cumulative GPA of 3.2 or higher</li><li>Intellectual curiosity</li><li>Planned graduation within one year of completing internship<br /><br /></li></ul><strong>Why Surya?<br /><br /></strong>Surya offers a competitive hourly wage, mentorship, and networking with company leaders.<br />Apply now and find out what it’s like to be valued for the talent and passion you invest in all that you do.<br /><br /><strong>Here Are a Few Things To Keep In Mind When Applying With Us<br /></strong><ul><li>You’ll be asked for information about your employment history and Educational Background</li><li>A recruiter will contact you by email or phone if you are under consideration for a current position</li><li>Position pays $10 per hour<br /><br /></li></ul>Equal Opportunity Employer<br /><br /></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Surya is a leading home decor company that has gained attention for its innovative designs and breadth of high quality home accessories. Products include rugs, pillows, throws, accent furniture, lighting, wall decor, decorative accents and bedding sold through a broad spectrum of global retailers, distributors, and interior designers. Surya fosters a work environment of creativity and collaboration and encourages each employee to take ownership in the company's growth. Surya has been named to the Inc.5000 list of America's fastest growing privately held companies for four years in a row.<br /><br />Other ways to connect with us:<br />facebook.com/suryasocial<br />pinterest.com/suryasocial<br />houzz.com/suryasocial<br />youtube.com/suryasocial<br />twitter.com/suryasocial</div>